    and responsibilities between the player (hereinafter \u201CUser\u201D) and Magic
    Thief Life (hereinafter \u201CGame\u201D).\n\nArticle 2 (Definitions)\n\u201CGame\u201D
    refers to Magic Thief Life, developed and published by POTENTIAL GAMES\u2122.\n\u201CAccount\u201D
    refers to the unique identifier created and managed by Steam.\n\u201CContent\u201D
    includes graphics, music, sound, scripts, characters, items, and other in-game
    assets.\n\u201CCheating\u201D refers to any action violating the game rules,
    including the use of cheats, hacks, or exploiting bugs.\n\nArticle 3 (License
    Grant)\nThe Game grants the User a limited license for personal, non-commercial
    use.\nThe User shall not copy, distribute, resell, rent, modify, reverse engineer,
    or hack the Game.\nThe license is temporary and may be terminated immediately
    upon violation of this Agreement.\n\nArticle 3-1 (Content Creation and Monetization)\nUsers
    may record or stream gameplay and may monetize their content on platforms such
    as YouTube or Twitch, including ad revenue, donations, or sponsorships. However,
    this does not permit unauthorized copying, redistribution, or commercial exploitation
    of derivative works of the game.\n\nArticle 4 (Account Management)\nAll account-related
    activities, including creation and login, are handled exclusively by Steam.\nUsers
    must comply with all Steam account management policies.\n\nArticle 5 (Account
    Responsibility)\nUsers are responsible for safeguarding their account passwords
    and personal information.\nSharing or using another person\u2019s account is
    strictly prohibited.\n\nArticle 6 (Cheating Prohibition)\nAny form of cheating,
    including hacks, exploits, or unauthorized modifications, is prohibited.\nIf
    cheating is detected, all in-game data will be forcibly reset.\n\nArticle 6-1
    (Anti-Cheat Program Access Scope)\nTo detect cheating, the game operates the
    NIGHTROL\u2122 anti-cheat program.\nNIGHTROL\u2122 only accesses the game-related
    memory and files within the installation folder, and does not access other programs,
    files, or personal information on the user\u2019s system.\nThe purpose of access
    is solely to detect cheating and protect game data, and collected information
    is limited to game data and cheating logs.\nThe program handles data securely
    using AES encryption, compression, and UTF-8 encoding.\n\nArticle 6-2 (Anti-Cheat
    Program Exceptions)\nNIGHTROL\u2122 only accesses game-related memory and files
    within the installation folder, and does not access system or personal data.\nFalse
    positives or functional limitations may occur due to other programs, security
    software, OS environment, or hardware configuration.\nData resets only apply
    to game-related data and do not affect system or personal data.\nIn regions with
    legal restrictions, certain features may be limited.\nGame data (e.g., data.json)
    is stored in a location deemed safe by the operating system. It does not access
    the user\u2019s system files, personal documents, or other program data.\n\nArticle
    7 (Data Reset)\nReset data includes but is not limited to:\n\nIn-game currency,
    items, and weapons\n\nPlayer data (e.g., number of burglaries)\n\nSettings (e.g.,
    mouse sensitivity, audio volume)\n\nOther relevant data (may be added in the
    future)\n\nUnrelated data is excluded.\nThe developer is not responsible for
    any data loss resulting from resets.\n\nArticle 8 (Paid Game)\nThis Game is a
    paid title with no in-app purchases.\nUsers should verify the purchase price
    and Steam policies before buying.\n\nArticle 9 (Refund Policy \u2013 Steam)\nSteam\u2019s
    official refund policy applies.\nRefunds may be requested within 14 days of purchase
    if the total playtime is less than 2 hours.\nDLC, gifts, and pre-orders may have
    separate rules.\nIf approved, refunds will be issued within one week via Steam
    Wallet or the original payment method.\n\nArticle 10 (Personal Information Collection
    and Use)\nAdditional personal data collected beyond Steam account info is limited
    to game statistics, cloud saves, and essential functions.\nAll collected information
    is securely managed according to applicable laws and Steam policies.\n\nArticle
    11 (Copyright \u2013 Game Content)\nAll rights to the Game\u2019s content belong
    to POTENTIAL GAMES\u2122.\nUnauthorized copying, distribution, secondary commercial
    use, rental, or resale is prohibited.\n\nArticle 12 (Copyright \u2013 Sound/Music)\nAll
    sounds, music, audio, graphics, characters, scripts, and other intellectual property
    rights are owned by the developer.\n\nArticle 13 (Disclaimer \u2013 General)\nThe
    Game is provided as a paid service, and the developer is not liable for any damage
    incurred during use.\nThis includes server maintenance, updates, bugs, or hardware
    issues.\n\nArticle 14 (Disclaimer \u2013 Data)\nThe developer is not responsible
    for data resets due to cheating detection or actions related to Steam refund
    compliance.\n\nArticle 15 (Modification of Terms and Notification)\nThe developer
    may modify this Agreement when necessary, and changes will take effect after
    prior notice.\nContinued use of the Game after changes implies acceptance of
    the modified terms.\n\nArticle 16 (Governing Law and Jurisdiction)\nAll disputes
    related to this Agreement or the use of the Game shall be governed by the laws
    of the Republic of Korea and resolved by the Seoul District Court.\n\nArticle
    17 (Developer and Team Members)\nDeveloper and Publisher: POTENTIAL GAMES\u2122\nDevelopment
    Team Members: An Jae Min, Lee Jae Won\n\nArticle 18 (Game Usage \u2013 UI)\nThe
    EULA is presented as scrollable text before starting the Game.\nUsers must scroll
    through the Agreement and click the checkbox to proceed.\nIf the User does not
    agree, the Game cannot be played.\n\nArticle 19 (DLC/Additional Content)\nFuture
    DLCs, gifts, and pre-orders are subject to separate rules.\nAll additional content
    is subject to this Agreement.\n\nArticle 20 (Special Circumstances)\nThe developer
    is not liable for exceptional situations such as bugs, server problems, or technical
    errors.\nThis includes issues arising from cheating and data resets.\n\nArticle
    21 (Legal Compliance)\nUsers must comply with applicable laws and Steam policies
    while using the Game.\nIllegal acts, copyright infringement, or account misuse
    may result in legal responsibility.\n\nArticle 22 (Other Provisions)\nMatters
    not specified in this Agreement shall comply with Steam policies, applicable
    laws, and developer regulations.\nThe developer may introduce additional clauses
    if necessary, which will be notified to users."
